Package com.gemalto.idp.mobile.oob

Class OobResultCode

java.lang.Object
com.gemalto.idp.mobile.oob.OobResultCode
public class OobResultCode extends Object
The definition of the OOB result codes.

It gathers the codes for OOB module, having one big list of potential problems.

Since:
4.0

  • Field Details

    • OOB_GENERIC_EXCEPTION

      public static final int OOB_GENERIC_EXCEPTION
      OOB reported error.

      This is the generic error code. It happen during internal process in OOB, probably means some system/low level error which requires an attention of the technical support.

      Client application actions:

      • Display error message.
      • Instruct end user to try again later and if the problem persists then contact his/her customer care.
      • To get more details (for technical support and/or customer care):
        • Collect more details about the problem from IdpResult.getUserInfo(String).
        • Collect stack trace from the IdpResult.getException().
      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values

    • OOB_SERVER_UNKNOWN_USER_ID

      public static final int OOB_SERVER_UNKNOWN_USER_ID
      OOB server does not know the specified user.

      Client application actions:

      • Display error message.
      • Instruct end user to check his/her user ID and try again.
      • Instruct end user, if the problem persists, to contact his/her customer care to check the validity of his/her user ID.
      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values

    • OOB_SERVER_REGISTRATION_FAILED_INVALID_CODE

      public static final int OOB_SERVER_REGISTRATION_FAILED_INVALID_CODE
      Registration to the OOB server failed: The registration code is not valid for the user ID.

      Client application actions:

      • Display error message.
      • Instruct end user to check his/her registration code and try again (note there may be limited number of attempts).
      • Instruct end user, if the problem persists, to contact his/her customer care to check the validity of his/her registration code.
      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values

    • OOB_SERVER_REGISTRATION_FAILED_EXPIRED

      public static final int OOB_SERVER_REGISTRATION_FAILED_EXPIRED
      Registration to the OOB server failed: The registration process expired.

      Client application actions:

      • Display error message.
      • Instruct end user to contact his/her customer care to re-initialize the registration process.
      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values

    • OOB_SERVER_COMMUNICATION_ERROR_NETWORK_OFF

      public static final int OOB_SERVER_COMMUNICATION_ERROR_NETWORK_OFF
      OOB reported error due to the unavailability of the device on network.

      Client application actions:

      • Display error message.
      • Instruct end user to enable some network connection (WiFi, GSM Data, ...), wait it to become really connected and repeat the operation.
      • To get more details (for technical support and/or customer care):
        • Collect more details about the problem from IdpResult.getUserInfo(String).
        • Collect stack trace from the IdpResult.getException().
      See Also:
